    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-23T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.33/1296/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-23T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 23, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>125. Your 413, April 8, [1941,] 1 p.m.<note n="97" xml:id="d208fn97">
                        <ref target="frus1941v02#pg_146">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 146</ref>.</note> It will be recalled
                    that the French Government in its note of April 8, 1941,<note n="98"
                        xml:id="d208fn98">Quoted in telegram No. 413.</note> informed the American
                    Embassy that it agreed to delay the preparation of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Dunkerque</hi> for departure from North Africa “until the conclusion of an
                    agreement on this subject”. It was further promised that the vessel in question
                    would not be moved without prior information.</p>
                <p>This Government was not informed of the recent intention to transfer the <hi
                        rend="italic">Dunkerque</hi> from Oran to Toulon. The action taken would
                    appear clearly to be a violation of this agreement. Please discuss this matter
                    urgently with the Foreign Minister, and telegraph his reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
